news.title: Kering sells majority stake in New York property in $900 million deal
news.para: Kering, the luxury powerhouse, is making waves by selling a substantial stake in a prime New York property in a deal worth $690 million with Ardian. This strategic sale is part of Kering's plan to manage its debt effectively. Prior to this, the company also divested its Paris real estate holdings.

news.title: Defaults on the rise in micro loans over property
news.para: According to the report, delinquency levels in the micro-LAP segment rose by 45 basis points (bps) year-on-year to 3.3% as of September 2025. Early delinquencies-measured as loans 90 days or more past due within 12 months on book-increased by 29 bps YoY to 2.2% for originations in the quarter ended September 2024. This is significantly higher than overall LAP early delinquencies of 1.6%.

news.title: Buffer zone dispute leaves Bengaluru development body site owners in limbo
news.para: Thousands of families face an indefinite wait as a forest land claim halts construction in Banashankari 6th Stage. Despite valid site allotments and decades of ownership, residents are unable to build or sell, citing a misinterpretation of forest buffer zone rules. Authorities promise resolution within months, but owners remain financially stranded.

news.title: Bombay HC cancels probate for ₹600 crore Bandra bungalow
news.para: Court finds it was obtained through concealment of facts, false statements about the deceased’s family; emphasised that even unintentional ignorance is no excuse

news.title: Rental farce using dodgy agreements turns out to be elaborate scheme to evade taxes
news.para: ​For several years, sub-tenants across multiple apartment complexes occupied flats under arrangements facilitated by Catena Homes. While rental agreements were shared with housing associations and uploaded on digital platforms such as myGate, the actual relationship was governed by separate lease agreements between Catena Homes and the sub-tenants

news.title: YEIDA increases minimum plot size to 40 sq metres for LIG housing scheme
news.para: YEIDA has increased the minimum plot size for its informal sector housing scheme from 30 to 40 sqm, citing viability and functional layout concerns. The annual income ceiling for eligibility has also been proposed to rise from Rs 3 lakh to Rs 8 lakh to include more beneficiaries. This policy shift aims to ensure safe and usable homes for allottees.

news.title: Telangana plans sale, regularisation of small housing board plots to boost revenue
news.para: The Telangana government is set to resolve land and revenue issues. Small housing board plots up to 100 square yards will be sold to homeowners. Additional land held by residents will be regularized. Leases and rentals will see stricter controls to safeguard public assets. The government aims to boost revenue and protect housing board properties from misuse.

news.title: Online registration for LIG & EWS flats starts in Ghaziabad
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) has launched an online registration service for low-income group (LIG) and economically weaker section (EWS) housing, open to private developers from December 15 to January 15, 2025.

news.title: Odisha RERA to hire civil engineer to boost buyers' protection & project transparency
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) is bringing in a civil engineer to rigorously inspect real estate projects across key cities. This move aims to bolster transparency and protect homebuyers by verifying project quality, safety, and adherence to approved plans. The authority is also onboarding a land expert to scrutinise plotting schemes, addressing recent concerns about unregistered projects.

news.title: Japan to expand rules on foreigners' property purchases: Finance minister
news.para: Japan will soon implement new rules regarding real estate transactions. From next April, international buyers looking to acquire homes must report their purchases to the authorities. This step aims to provide a clearer understanding of foreign ownership in the real estate sector, addressing mounting worries about speculative buying practices.

news.title: European Union to unveil plan to tackle housing crisis
news.para: The EU will on Tuesday present a first-ever plan to address the continent's deepening housing crisis, aiming to boost construction and regulate short-term rentals. "This is getting more traction than we expected," a commission official told AFP.

news.title: MTNL board approves sale of residential block in BKC Mumbai to Nabard for ₹350.72 crore
news.para: MTNL's board has just ticked off a major milestone in its asset monetization strategy! They’ve sanctioned the sale of a prime residential property in Mumbai's trendy Bandra Kurla Complex to NABARD for a staggering Rs 350.72 crore.

news.title: Champaran: Arrest warrants against 140 brick kiln operators for outstanding government dues
news.para: Arrest warrants have been issued for 140 brick kiln operators in East Champaran for outstanding dues exceeding Rs27 crore in mining fees and royalty tax. The district auction officer warned that no laxity will be tolerated in recovering these long-overdue amounts, even from deceased defaulters' heirs. Operators are urged to deposit dues to avoid arrest and property confiscation.

news.title: China Vanke to hold second bondholder meeting after debt-extension plan rejected
news.para: China Vanke is gearing up for an important decision day on Thursday, where bondholders will cast their votes on whether to extend the repayment deadline for a 2 billion yuan bond. This follows the earlier refusal for a one-year extension. Furthermore, Vanke is also pursuing a prolongation for an additional bond totaling 3.7 billion yuan.

news.title: Case filed in alleged resort land investment fraud in Udupi
news.para: A Kerala-based transport professional and his associates were allegedly defrauded of several lakhs of rupees by individuals promising land for a resort development along the Udupi coast. The complainants were persuaded to invest in a venture, with payments made to various accounts and individuals before the deal soured and threats were allegedly issued.

news.title: Rates slashed, Chandigarh civic body begins process to rent out vacant shops
news.para: The Municipal Corporation has reduced rents by 25% on hundreds of commercial properties to fill prolonged vacancies. This decision follows multiple failed auction attempts for various sites, including shops, booths, and kiosks. The move aims to generate revenue and reduce maintenance costs for the civic body.

news.title: Police intensify action against illegal sand mining, quarrying in Udupi
news.para: Udupi police have intensified efforts to combat illegal sand mining and quarrying by establishing 29 check posts and conducting round-the-clock vehicle inspections. Since December 6, 3,966 vehicles have been checked, with action taken against 11 for transporting materials without proper permits and royalty payments. Authorities are committed to continuing strict enforcement against unauthorized material transport.

news.title: 360 ONE real assets platform raises ₹2,300 crore
news.para: In a remarkable feat, 360 ONE Asset's real assets platform has amassed ₹2,300 crore within just four months, showcasing its strong appeal to investors. This fund primarily focuses on acquiring infrastructure and income-generating commercial ventures.

news.title: Concorde invests ₹125 crore to develop commercial block at Concorde Mayfair in Bengaluru
news.para: Bengaluru's Concorde has invested ₹125 crore to develop a commercial block at Concorde Mayfair. This new development in Yelahanka will feature retail spaces and office units.

news.title: Income tax department conducts searches at Brigade Enterprises' premises
news.para: Brigade Enterprises shares dropped after the Income Tax Department conducted search operations. The searches concluded recently. The company stated its operations are unaffected. Analysts maintain a strong buy rating with a significant target price. The company recently acquired land in Hyderabad. Brigade Enterprises reported strong September quarter results with increased profit and revenue.
